<br>
The mana regen is wonderful when combined with your pet and even better with a KEI or some buff like that.  Combine it with a mount and you're really doing great.  The first thing I do after a rez is loot the epic and the drum, summon my drogmor (if I'm outside) and use the epic, and then I go back to looting my corpse (if my harvest button didn't pop in which case, I harvest).  Also, the main consideration for the epic is the money you save on buying peridots.  When you're level 51 you're only buying jasper but manashield is a spell worth having if you don't have your epic and it takes dots.  I was a poor wizzy trying very hard to save while having to buy those dots.  The epic aggro is less than the manashield aggro.<br>
<br>
They tell me that I'm somewhat lucky I have mine.  I started the quest when I was 51 and finished it within 8 months at level 52.  I'm in a small family guild that cannot do raids for the Broken Golem or Venril Sathir.  We did do Kedge forever though.  My guildmates were so happy when Phinny finally gave me the staff.  They never wanted to go back there again.  I was in a raid with another guild when they decided to do the BG for me. I just multi quested the staff from Venril Sathir because I was unable to get into a raid for him and my guild was too small for it.  It took me a long time to save enough money to start looking for the mq but I got it. <p>Renia - wizardess of Cazic-Thule<br>
Baroness of MoY who aspires to greatness (and may attain it one day).</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sardonus>Sardonus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/03 11:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: also...</span><hr size=1> &quot;And I think the Wand of Musing is wildly inferior to the epic as a constant mainhand item. Losing all those resists and stats for FT1 might work if all you do is quadkite, but in any other environment, I'd rather have the Staff of the Four equipped. I'd carry it for use during downtime, though. &quot;<br>
<br>
I guess we'll disagree here then. Resists dont' mean anything in day to day exp grinds in Tier2/3. The sta and dex bonus mean to incredibly little imo. The extra hp's are nice but, fighting in PoP, those hp's aren't gonna make a difference. For my regular exp grinds, any flowing thought is better than the stats on the epic.<br>
<br>
For raids, I sometimes swap epic in. What I'm finding though is that even on raids I'm still more limited by my mana/aggro than anything else. We raid places like ToV where my other resist gear is sufficient. In that case, the wand is still more useful to me. The stuff we do in PoP that ae's and such, where resists matter alot, I'm finding that as long as I stay in range of the bards my other resist gear is more than sufficient as well. In that case again, the extra stats from the epic are if little use to me. Just about the only time I wear the epic for extended periods is when we are raiding PoP mobs that ae where we don't have a bard around.<br>
<br>
And, since you alluded to it, I haven't quadded since I was 54. If I wanted to solo I'd go play a game designed/intended for it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bicrius>Bicrius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 300<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/21/03 11:25 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: is the epic still worth it?</span><hr size=1> The wizard epic is still, and always will be a worthwhile item. By all means, get it. I've had mine for a year and a half, and it's been worth it, every second. <p><center><table border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1">
